title: On Gophers Week, UMD Has Extra Edge
text:
On Gophers Week, UMD Has Extra Edge 
By Zach Schneider October 14, 2015 Updated Oct 14, 2015 at 10:05 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) senior defenseman Andy Welinski smiled on Wednesday afternoon as he said the team prepares for every opponent in the same way, but it was obvious he wanted to say something else. 
When the opponent is Minnesota, there's always something extra. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
"There's obviously a little extra energy," he said, still smiling. "A lot of the guys know each other, and there's the tradition of this rivalry." 
Welinski, a native of Duluth, Minn., has played several games against the Gophers, including winning four of five games in this rivalry a year ago. 
For Hermantown, Minn. native Neal Pionk, however, this weekend's home-and-home series will be his first taste of the intrastate rivalry. 
"I think it's going to be very energetic. Obviously, Minnesota is a respected rivalry of ours," Pionk said. "I knew as a kid growing up it was a big game and a hot ticket. I'm excited to see the atmosphere." 
Friday's series opener will start at 7:07 p.m. at Mariucci Arena, while Saturday's game will start at 7:07 p.m. at AMSOIL Arena.
